    "description": "The Dolphin Board is a PCI-card that provides a standard definition/high definition serial digital interface. This is the Doremi decoder card that contains the JPEG-2000 decoder hardware and BNC serial digital interface connectors used in the Doremi DCP-2000 Digital Cinema Server. The Dolphin Board utilizes a dual-link encoded serial digital interface for output of DCIcompliant resolutions up to 2040x1080p24 (2K-film). It can also operate single link for lower resolution material (i.e., trailers, advertisements, etc.).",
